[node name="Gameplay" type="RichTextLabel" parent="Background/Info/Tutorials"]
visible = false
custom_minimum_size = Vector2(450, 350)
layout_mode = 2
text = "Welcome to Bullet Hell! The goal of the game is to dodge bullets and shoot enemies to survive as long as possible. You can collect items and you have a set number of lives.

The profile menu will show you your total stats, such as:
 - Kills.
 - Deaths.
 - Time alive. 
 - Etc...

The settings menu is where you go to change your preferences. You can change anything from video settings, to difficulty, sound settings, and controls."

[node name="Player" type="RichTextLabel" parent="Background/Info/Tutorials"]
visible = false
custom_minimum_size = Vector2(450, 350)
layout_mode = 2
text = "The player is the character that you move around the game to keep alive. The player has a set speed and damage, and power ups will change those temporarily. Everytime your player dies, you lose a life. If you have one life left and you die, the game ends. You start with 3 lives.

You takes damage from colliding with enemies and enemy projectiles.

You pick up power ups by colliding with them.

You cannot exit world bounds!"

[node name="Enemies" type="RichTextLabel" parent="Background/Info/Tutorials"]
visible = false
custom_minimum_size = Vector2(450, 350)
layout_mode = 2
text = "The enemies are the characters you need to try to eliminate. They spawn randomly, and they are a pest to the Bullet Hell world. Be careful though! There are some mighty enemies called 'Bosses', and they're quite tough. Kill them by attacking with your projectiles. Use those power ups to help you!

Enemies spawn randomly at random locations.

Enemies are damaged by friendly projectiles.

Enemies cannot escape world bounds."

[node name="PowerUps" type="RichTextLabel" parent="Background/Info/Tutorials"]
visible = false
custom_minimum_size = Vector2(450, 350)
layout_mode = 2
text = "Power ups is what you need to get ahead in the game of Bullet Hell! They are items that increase your abilites, and can be picked up in the game. Power ups spawn randomly at random locations and they are one-time use. Be on the lookout for those! You can increase your abilities such as:
 - Running speed.
 - Damage.
 - Health.
 - Lives.

Power ups spawn within world bounds randomly, and at random locations.

Power ups can only by picked up by a player.

Power ups picked up are counted in the profile menu.

Power ups help you win the game!"

[node name="Projectiles" type="RichTextLabel" parent="Background/Info/Tutorials"]
visible = false
custom_minimum_size = Vector2(450, 350)
layout_mode = 2
text = "Projectiles, also known as bullets, are flying entities that can cause damage to either the player or enemies. Projectiles are mainly used by the enemies to try to eliminate the player. Projectiles are also used by the player to damage enemies. When a player collides with an enemy projectile, you lose health, and the same goes for the enemy when they collide with your projectile.

There are two types of projectiles:
 - Enemy.
 - Friendly.

Only friendly projectiles damage enemies.

Only enemy projectiles damge you."

